<paragraph id="AECF8D82F8973244DD68A61A8E4949FA" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D7F8CE25F04F7B68790837EF8E4CF881" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">
This genus includes 28 species distributed mainly in Asia and Africa. Half of them have been recorded from China, mainly in Yunnan and Guangxi provinces (
<bibRefCitation id="DD0627B30E388E258DD1FF025C4B093D" author="Li, SQ" journalOrPublisher="Science Press, Beijing" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" refId="B7" refString="Li, SQ, Lin, YC, 2016. Species Catalogue of China. Vol. 2. Animals. Invertebrates (1). Arachnida: Araneae. Science Press, Beijing" title="Species Catalogue of China. Vol. 2. Animals. Invertebrates (1). Arachnida: Araneae." year="2016">Li and Lin 2016</bibRefCitation>
), but two species are known only from females and three from males.
</paragraph>
